==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[n00b]]
*[[newb]]
*[[nub]] 

===Noun===
'''"Noob"''' essentially means "newbie", a new player or someone who has recently joined something. However "noob" is often used in an insulting fashion. A noob is essentially a newbie, but a noob is also regarded as an idiot.

'''noob'''
# (''internet'') (''derogatory'') a [[newbie]]
#: ''Noobs are annoying, they never know the [[forum]] rules.''
# (''gaming'') (''derogatory'') someone who plays at a beginner level
#: ''You just got [[pwned]], noob.''

